{
  "text": "H 2 S can be generated in numerous pathways-both enzymatically and non-enzymatically and from various substrates beyond cysteine [CITATION_1] . The main pathway by which E. coli generate H 2 S when grown aerobically in nutrient rich LB is via 3MST, encoded by mstA [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Phenotypic consequences of decreased H 2 S production include greater susceptibility to multiple classes of antibiotics and H 2 O 2 3,4,7 . However, we discovered that antibiotics-sensitive strain \u0394mstA reverted to the resistant phenotype of the isogenic parent when challenged with different antibiotics. The \u0394mstA variant, referred to as",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5259764",
